WEBVTT

00:00:46.420 --> 00:00:47.820
Don't retreat!

00:00:47.820 --> 00:00:49.250
Protect the villagers!

00:01:58.260 --> 00:02:05.350
Beyond Journey's End

00:03:02.940 --> 00:03:05.950
Episode 34: A Demon-Slaying Request

00:03:05.940 --> 00:03:12.960
30 years after the death of Himmel the Hero,
in the Rufen region, located on the Northern Plateau

00:03:28.060 --> 00:03:29.930
Please.

00:03:30.190 --> 00:03:33.000
I have a son. He's still a child.

00:03:35.610 --> 00:03:36.860
Silence.

00:03:37.920 --> 00:03:42.320
I've heard those words
more times than I can count.

00:04:05.260 --> 00:04:09.330
So, where is this son of yours?

00:04:10.340 --> 00:04:13.780
At least try telling half-truths.

00:04:29.400 --> 00:04:33.540
I received a demon-slaying request
directly from Ms. Serie.

00:04:33.540 --> 00:04:35.520
I didn't know what I'd find,

00:04:36.370 --> 00:04:40.160
but it seems to be my hometown
in ruins after a demon attack.

00:04:44.740 --> 00:04:51.170
I bear no attachment to this place,
but it's still sad seeing it like this.

00:05:03.760 --> 00:05:06.060
Is that you, Genau?

00:05:07.120 --> 00:05:08.030
Yes.

00:05:11.420 --> 00:05:15.110
Genau. Demons destroyed the village...

00:05:16.080 --> 00:05:19.370
I know. I've already taken care of them.

00:05:19.370 --> 00:05:21.420
I killed them all.

00:05:24.470 --> 00:05:26.610
What about the others?

00:05:30.480 --> 00:05:33.150
They're safe. All of them.

00:05:34.090 --> 00:05:35.700
You'll be okay, too.

00:05:36.830 --> 00:05:41.650
A newly qualified
first-class mage came with me.

00:05:42.690 --> 00:05:47.000
She's a mage, but she can
use the Goddess's magic.

00:05:47.460 --> 00:05:49.190
Unusual, right?

00:05:49.880 --> 00:05:52.810
She'll heal your wounds right away.

00:05:53.300 --> 00:05:55.700
You'll be able to reopen your shop soon.

00:05:57.440 --> 00:06:01.700
Have you finally learned
to bake decent bread?

00:06:02.620 --> 00:06:06.550
I've only been able to eat
cold, hard bread recently.

00:06:06.550 --> 00:06:09.710
I'd love to have something freshly baked.

00:06:10.670 --> 00:06:15.000
In truth, it doesn't
even have to be fresh.

00:06:15.460 --> 00:06:19.170
I'd gladly take unsold leftovers
or loaves like your old failures.

00:06:20.570 --> 00:06:22.220
I'm not picky.

00:06:38.060 --> 00:06:39.310
Mr. Genau.

00:06:44.290 --> 00:06:46.240
Bring the injured over here.

00:06:46.240 --> 00:06:49.430
"Injured"? You don't need
to spare my feelings, Methode.

00:06:50.030 --> 00:06:53.300
He's already dead.

00:06:55.090 --> 00:06:58.770
He was beyond saving
when I found him.

00:06:59.530 --> 00:07:01.350
The stench is dreadful, isn't it?

00:07:01.950 --> 00:07:04.790
His stomach wound was
already starting to rot.

00:07:05.200 --> 00:07:07.620
Someone like that can't be saved.

00:07:08.580 --> 00:07:12.790
But he still clung to me.

00:07:27.010 --> 00:07:29.450
He was a baker's son.

00:07:30.190 --> 00:07:33.310
We often played together as children.

00:07:34.540 --> 00:07:38.470
He took over the shop
after his father passed,

00:07:39.060 --> 00:07:42.440
but his bread wasn't very good.

00:07:45.290 --> 00:07:47.370
I won't get to eat it anymore.

00:07:49.890 --> 00:07:53.200
Everyone's together now,
so he won't be lonely.

00:07:55.380 --> 00:07:59.480
Why does it have to be them
instead of us?

00:08:00.520 --> 00:08:06.560
Unlike us, the people of this village
didn't choose to fight.

00:08:16.810 --> 00:08:18.770
If anyone has to die,

00:08:18.770 --> 00:08:23.640
it should be the first-class mages
like us who chose this path.

00:08:23.640 --> 00:08:25.070
Mr. Genau.

00:08:26.970 --> 00:08:29.800
By the time the request from
the Chivalric Order of Norm

00:08:29.800 --> 00:08:32.460
stationed here reached
the northern branch,

00:08:32.460 --> 00:08:34.730
this village had already been destroyed.

00:08:36.490 --> 00:08:39.290
You're not responsible for what happened.

00:08:41.060 --> 00:08:43.270
I'm going to look around
the village again.

00:08:46.680 --> 00:08:49.930
Perhaps you should rest a bit.

00:08:51.070 --> 00:08:52.230
Why?

00:08:52.230 --> 00:08:53.540
Why? Because...

00:08:56.080 --> 00:08:57.300
Quiet.

00:08:58.080 --> 00:09:00.460
One of my eyes was just put out.

00:09:01.080 --> 00:09:06.430
One warrior and one hidden mage—
no, two mages?

00:09:07.290 --> 00:09:08.530
Two.

00:09:09.100 --> 00:09:12.690
They're quite skilled.
Do you think they're enemies?

00:09:18.150 --> 00:09:20.430
No, they're probably...

00:09:31.870 --> 00:09:34.180
Oh, it's you, Frieren.

00:09:35.670 --> 00:09:40.440
Which means the other one I detected
was Fern the first-class mage.

00:09:42.500 --> 00:09:44.260
Who do we have here?

00:09:44.260 --> 00:09:47.710
Methode, and one of the proctors
from the first-class mage exam...

00:09:48.110 --> 00:09:49.830
Genau, right?

00:09:50.480 --> 00:09:55.870
Honestly, there was so much bloodlust in
that spell, I thought you were a demon.

00:09:57.330 --> 00:10:01.540
Was there? My apologies for the confusion.

00:10:02.260 --> 00:10:05.530
She's right. I was worried to death.

00:10:06.180 --> 00:10:08.890
Fern, it's okay. They're on our side.

00:10:08.890 --> 00:10:10.550
Let Stark know.

00:10:10.550 --> 00:10:11.460
Okay.

00:10:15.550 --> 00:10:16.790
I see.

00:10:16.790 --> 00:10:20.610
So Ms. Fern also received
a demon-slaying request.

00:10:21.130 --> 00:10:23.300
We were on the Northern Plateau anyway.

00:10:23.670 --> 00:10:26.550
So, what's the situation?

00:10:38.100 --> 00:10:39.900
Are you praying?

00:10:40.180 --> 00:10:41.370
Is that a problem?

00:10:41.760 --> 00:10:44.400
No, I don't think so.

00:10:44.870 --> 00:10:47.420
My village was destroyed by demons, too.

00:10:48.780 --> 00:10:49.860
I see.

00:10:52.850 --> 00:10:53.670
Hey.

00:10:54.460 --> 00:10:57.100
Demons eat humans, right?

00:10:58.850 --> 00:11:01.130
So why are the bodies still here?

00:11:01.680 --> 00:11:03.550
It was the same at my village.

00:11:04.060 --> 00:11:07.150
Who knows? Not me, at least.

00:11:07.150 --> 00:11:10.310
They kill humans even when they're full.

00:11:11.440 --> 00:11:13.150
I wonder why.

00:11:14.920 --> 00:11:19.710
I see. The two of you defeated
the demons in the village.

00:11:19.710 --> 00:11:22.480
We were a bit too late.

00:11:22.480 --> 00:11:25.070
We even hurried here.

00:11:25.450 --> 00:11:29.640
There's still one loose end
that Mr. Genau wishes to tie up.

00:11:36.760 --> 00:11:39.940
These are what remains of the Chivalric
Order of Norm that was stationed here.

00:11:39.940 --> 00:11:41.440
The Chivalric Order of Norm?

00:11:41.930 --> 00:11:44.620
We saw them in Norm Company
territory, remember?

00:11:44.620 --> 00:11:47.490
They're the trading company's
military force.

00:11:48.670 --> 00:11:51.000
There are so few of them.

00:11:51.480 --> 00:11:54.600
This is the standard amount
to station in a village this size.

00:11:55.130 --> 00:11:59.930
Even then, they were far better
soldiers than the village deserved.

00:12:01.540 --> 00:12:03.680
This was their captain.

00:12:04.190 --> 00:12:07.740
He was a great man who defended
the village for years.

00:12:10.510 --> 00:12:15.010
I'm surprised.
He was far stronger than Stark.

00:12:15.320 --> 00:12:18.010
That's not a high bar to clear.

00:12:19.020 --> 00:12:21.320
What was the cause of death?

00:12:21.320 --> 00:12:26.640
An autopsy spell revealed
that they were killed by blades.

00:12:27.020 --> 00:12:28.820
They all died instantly.

00:12:29.890 --> 00:12:35.170
The demons in the village were weaklings
who'd have stood no chance against them.

00:12:36.780 --> 00:12:40.400
The one who attacked the village
is probably still alive.

00:12:41.760 --> 00:12:46.540
Good news. You didn't come here in vain.

00:12:48.350 --> 00:12:52.650
I see. Looks like there's still
something we can do to help.

00:12:54.490 --> 00:12:59.000
Let's show it how terrifying
humanity can be.

00:13:08.760 --> 00:13:12.930
Like this, this, this...

00:13:13.860 --> 00:13:15.260
and then this, perhaps?

00:13:17.820 --> 00:13:20.770
Those are pretty unrealistic movements.

00:13:21.180 --> 00:13:24.760
But based on the knights' wounds...

00:13:25.840 --> 00:13:27.490
Maybe...

00:13:28.920 --> 00:13:30.910
it fought with two swords.

00:13:34.080 --> 00:13:35.660
In that case...

00:13:37.930 --> 00:13:43.200
Typically, demons only conceal
their mana for short periods of time,

00:13:43.200 --> 00:13:47.290
so we can assume it's currently
outside mana detection range.

00:13:47.620 --> 00:13:50.660
So the immediate area
around this village is safe.

00:13:51.250 --> 00:13:57.050
Genau told me where demons are likely
to establish bases around here,

00:13:57.050 --> 00:13:59.310
so we'll focus our search there.

00:13:59.670 --> 00:14:00.530
Okay.

00:14:10.830 --> 00:14:13.360
But first, we should have dinner.

00:14:13.690 --> 00:14:16.300
You can't fight on an empty stomach.

00:14:23.200 --> 00:14:25.490
This bread again?

00:14:26.750 --> 00:14:29.960
We'll just have to be patient until the
logistics network is reestablished.

00:14:32.270 --> 00:14:33.230
Where is Genau?

00:14:34.120 --> 00:14:36.710
Still at the church, I believe.

00:14:36.710 --> 00:14:39.550
I'll bring his share of the bread to him.

00:14:39.780 --> 00:14:43.790
Actually, could you tell me
your analysis of the enemy?

00:14:43.790 --> 00:14:46.270
I'd like to know their composition first.

00:14:46.740 --> 00:14:48.900
I'll deliver the bread, then.

00:14:50.300 --> 00:14:51.760
Thank you.

00:14:53.720 --> 00:14:56.270
So, what's your analysis?

00:14:57.040 --> 00:15:01.960
It will take some more time to accurately
determine their composition,

00:15:01.960 --> 00:15:03.960
but there's something I know already.

00:15:04.410 --> 00:15:07.830
I see. Then let's hold a strategy...

00:15:17.110 --> 00:15:20.350
Actually, maybe we should eat first.

00:15:28.100 --> 00:15:30.490
What? Are we heading out already?

00:15:31.000 --> 00:15:34.080
No. It's time for dinner.

00:15:40.200 --> 00:15:41.560
It's hard.

00:15:42.050 --> 00:15:45.670
Sure is. What were you doing?

00:15:46.910 --> 00:15:51.090
The demon attack destroyed
the church's barrier.

00:15:51.610 --> 00:15:54.630
I replaced it with a stronger one.

00:15:55.430 --> 00:15:58.360
The villagers' bodies
are inside, after all.

00:15:59.260 --> 00:16:02.930
Hey, why are you just leaving them there?

00:16:03.500 --> 00:16:05.590
I'll help you bury them.

00:16:05.960 --> 00:16:07.780
I'm good at manual labor.

00:16:08.250 --> 00:16:09.650
I see.

00:16:09.650 --> 00:16:13.180
I suppose someone not from the
Northern Plateau wouldn't understand.

00:16:16.290 --> 00:16:19.980
In general, villages on the Northern
Plateau don't have graveyards.

00:16:21.620 --> 00:16:25.730
If they do, they're tucked into
corners of sturdy fortress cities,

00:16:26.490 --> 00:16:30.170
or they're nobles' graves
protected by barriers.

00:16:30.650 --> 00:16:33.330
Everyone else is buried
in common graveyards

00:16:33.330 --> 00:16:36.930
at the Plateau's southern edge,
where there are fewer monsters.

00:16:37.310 --> 00:16:39.760
They go to the trouble
of transporting them there

00:16:40.730 --> 00:16:43.170
with a Chivalric Order of Norm escort.

00:16:44.440 --> 00:16:46.380
Do you know why?

00:16:46.380 --> 00:16:47.690
No.

00:16:48.540 --> 00:16:53.560
Because if they're not careful,
the smell of decay attracts monsters.

00:16:54.620 --> 00:16:56.910
It's a hellish sight.

00:16:57.360 --> 00:16:59.450
Not even the bones are left behind.

00:17:00.950 --> 00:17:06.560
For a while now, the Norm Company has
been insisting people cremate their dead.

00:17:07.730 --> 00:17:11.400
It's the kind of rational thinking
you'd expect from merchants.

00:17:11.400 --> 00:17:13.220
I agree with them.

00:17:17.990 --> 00:17:21.210
But the clergy have voiced
their opposition.

00:17:21.780 --> 00:17:26.220
I understand how they feel. Painfully so.

00:17:27.020 --> 00:17:32.290
It's inhumane to suggest burning people
who already suffered painful deaths.

00:17:35.660 --> 00:17:38.230
But it's something we'll
eventually have to accept.

00:17:38.760 --> 00:17:43.120
Soon enough, no one will be able
to rest in their homeland either way.

00:17:54.430 --> 00:17:57.940
This really isn't how
eating bread should sound.

00:17:58.420 --> 00:18:03.510
It feels somehow strange
to be sharing a meal like this.

00:18:04.000 --> 00:18:10.310
Honestly, I never expected us
to meet again here.

00:18:10.310 --> 00:18:11.780
Neither did we.

00:18:13.200 --> 00:18:15.810
We received the demon-slaying request

00:18:15.810 --> 00:18:18.940
while we were camping on the
other side of the mountains.

00:18:18.940 --> 00:18:21.030
It really took me by surprise.

00:18:28.300 --> 00:18:30.460
Who's this little guy?

00:18:30.460 --> 00:18:32.350
He's holding a letter.

00:18:33.780 --> 00:18:37.470
What are you and Genau doing here?

00:18:37.920 --> 00:18:43.300
I find it hard to believe two other first-
class mages just happened to be nearby.

00:18:43.630 --> 00:18:47.410
Ms. Serie instructed me
to come to the Northern Plateau

00:18:47.410 --> 00:18:53.090
and slay demons with Mr. Genau.
So I'm here on her orders.

00:18:53.660 --> 00:18:57.330
I didn't know first-class mages
had those kinds of obligations.

00:18:57.330 --> 00:18:59.200
I'm glad I didn't become one.

00:18:59.500 --> 00:19:02.940
It's actually something
I'm doing as her student.

00:19:03.350 --> 00:19:04.450
Her student?

00:19:04.850 --> 00:19:11.740
Yes. Typically, first-class mages
become Ms. Serie's students.

00:19:11.740 --> 00:19:14.540
Come to think of it,
I heard something about that.

00:19:14.830 --> 00:19:16.930
I turned her down.

00:19:16.930 --> 00:19:18.910
You're a good girl, Fern.

00:19:19.670 --> 00:19:23.750
So that's why the two of you gave in
to Serie's unreasonable demands.

00:19:23.750 --> 00:19:25.250
She must be running you ragged.

00:19:25.250 --> 00:19:27.430
I wouldn't say that.

00:19:28.080 --> 00:19:31.390
If anything, I only wish
I could be more useful to her.

00:19:32.600 --> 00:19:35.930
She's so small and cute, you know?

00:19:36.620 --> 00:19:38.410
Is she?

00:19:38.410 --> 00:19:42.460
Of course, you're just
as cute, Ms. Frieren.

00:19:43.020 --> 00:19:44.620
Thanks...

00:19:46.310 --> 00:19:50.960
And Mr. Genau has been a perfect
example of how not to behave.

00:19:51.900 --> 00:19:55.150
Don't end up like me.

00:19:58.190 --> 00:20:00.960
Well, now that we've eaten,

00:20:01.830 --> 00:20:04.100
let's hold that strategy meeting.

00:20:05.900 --> 00:20:09.460
How's the analysis of
the enemy coming along?

00:20:09.460 --> 00:20:10.200
Well...

00:20:10.610 --> 00:20:12.190
Have you learned anything?

00:20:12.590 --> 00:20:17.810
Yeah. She's still figuring out
exactly how many there are,

00:20:18.320 --> 00:20:20.560
but we did learn one thing.

00:20:22.770 --> 00:20:25.620
Didn't you say the enemy
fought with two swords?

00:20:25.620 --> 00:20:26.940
Actually...

00:20:27.970 --> 00:20:34.400
That was our initial theory,
but it didn't quite add up.

00:20:34.820 --> 00:20:36.290
What do you mean?

00:20:36.290 --> 00:20:40.660
As far as I know,
most dual-wielding styles

00:20:40.660 --> 00:20:44.670
emphasize a balance between
attacking and defending.

00:20:45.040 --> 00:20:48.370
Typically, one blade is a longsword
for inflicting fatal blows,

00:20:48.370 --> 00:20:52.120
while the other is a more
maneuverable shortsword.

00:20:54.230 --> 00:20:58.400
In other words, there should naturally
be a difference in the cuts inflicted.

00:21:02.030 --> 00:21:06.400
Could it be an incredibly strong demon
who wields two large swords?

00:21:06.690 --> 00:21:08.930
We did consider that assumption

00:21:08.930 --> 00:21:12.320
and attempted to recreate the
same cuts based on the marks

00:21:12.320 --> 00:21:14.960
left on the dead and the
field of battle, but...

00:21:16.670 --> 00:21:21.410
A dual-wielding style still resulted
in unrealistic movements.

00:21:22.330 --> 00:21:26.460
What comes next is still
only speculation, but...

00:21:27.940 --> 00:21:29.540
Just tell us.

00:21:32.850 --> 00:21:34.310
Oh, sorry.

00:21:34.310 --> 00:21:35.300
Excuse me.

00:21:48.610 --> 00:21:49.820
The enemy wields...

00:21:50.740 --> 00:21:52.320
four blades.

00:21:54.390 --> 00:21:55.580
I see.

00:21:56.470 --> 00:22:00.070
Apparently, it was the natural
conclusion based on the cut marks

00:22:00.070 --> 00:22:02.320
on the knights' bodies
and surrounding buildings.

00:22:08.420 --> 00:22:10.210
Four blades...

00:22:20.900 --> 00:22:25.030
Translation
Sho Stifler
Editing & Typesetting
Geoff Mazzolini
Subtitle Timing
Edgar Cruz
Quality Check
Alicia Ashby
Translation Check
Elizabeth Ellis

00:23:49.980 --> 00:23:51.770
He's better than me.

00:23:50.210 --> 00:23:52.570
We can handle that many.

00:23:50.880 --> 00:23:53.800
You can't run away, though.
You'd be abandoning the village.

00:23:52.150 --> 00:23:53.130
Shall we begin?

00:23:53.130 --> 00:23:55.530
You seem to know who I am.

00:23:53.840 --> 00:23:55.530
She should be fun.

00:23:54.720 --> 00:23:57.670
It's likely that it has
a far-from-human appearance.

00:23:55.700 --> 00:23:58.250
One of them was a demon general.

00:23:58.040 --> 00:23:59.940
Episode 35
The Divine Revolte

00:23:58.250 --> 00:23:59.940
The Divine Revolte.

